# Financial Risk Market VaR For Date Of Second Largest Daily Loss Amount

## identifier
de8053

## type
float

## definition
This is the value at risk (VaR), calculated as at the business day preceding the date the second largest daily loss was experienced by the reporting party over the relevant period due to market movements.

VaR is a technique used to estimate the likelihood of losses in a portfolio based on analysis of historical price movements and volatilities.

For the purposes of this item the amount reported is the 99% one-day VaR number calculated as at the previous business day.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=FinancialRisk.Market.VaRForDateOfSecondLargestDailyLoss.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.06
- period=duration
